<L>__{exterior fleet prison day}
<A>__{his mother, now very old and hobbled with arthritis, enters the prison, carrying a basket on her arm.}
<C>__{narrator}
<D>__{his faithful old mother joined him in his lonely exile, and had a bedroom in fleet market over the way. she would come and stay the whole day with him in prison working.}
<L>__{interior castle hackton countess' study}
<A>__{signing a payment draft, the countess sighs and gazes out of the large window.}
<C>__{narrator}
<D>__{the countess was never out of love with her husband, and, as long as she lived, james enjoyed his income of 300 pounds per year and was, perhaps, as happy in prison, as at any period of his existence.}
